FBIS4-14527 "drsov063_r_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-063 Daily Report 31 Mar 1994 Azerbaijan Parliament Discusses Worsening Economic Situation Parliament Discusses Worsening Economic Situation NC3103205894 Baku TURAN in English 1807 GMT 31 Mar 94 NC3103205894 Baku TURAN English BFN [Text] Baku (March 31) TURAN -- Today's session of Milli Majlis is to discuss socio-economic situation in the Republic. According to independent experts, since January 1994 Azerbaijan's economy was enveloped by hyperinflation. For three months of 1994 the inflation totalled 50-60 per cent, prices increased by more than three times. State budget has yet to be adopted. At the beginning of March, 1994, Milli Majlis adopted the resolution to hear the account of the government. According to several sources, the Cabinet is not ready to Parliamentary hearings.
